The paper discusses the optimization of data transmissions in Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs) using forecasting algorithms, which falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The use of Dual Prediction Schemes (DPSs) also involves the application of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of statistical theorems to describe the expected impact of DPSs and data aggregation, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The optimization of data transmissions in WSNs also involves the use of control systems (cs.SY) to manage the flow of data. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of various parameters on the performance of the system, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
